wfweb CHANGELOG
===============

This changelog covers wfweb changes only. wfweb is a fork of wfview that adds
a built-in web interface. See https://gitlab.com/eliggett/wfview for the
upstream wfview history.


v0.6.0 (2026-04-25)
--------------------

Packet (AX.25 / APRS / Terminal):
- Add full packet station: live AX.25 frame monitor, connected-mode QSOs,
  APRS heard-stations + beacon compose, and YAPP file transfer
- Vendored Dire Wolf modem subset (300/1200 AFSK, 9600 G3RUH FSK) wired
  into the web server; runs entirely server-side over the existing mic
  and RX audio paths
- Tabbed UI with MONITOR, RX/TX waterfall, and frame-type display
- Tabbed terminal sessions with auto-select for the sole session, visible
  connection state, selectable scrollback, and clickable callsigns that
  populate the peer field
- Real YAPP framing per IW3FQG spec; transfers show progress + abort and
  gate completion on peer AF
- AX.25 link layer: connected-mode address slots, CSMA + per-baud T1,
  basic digipeating, force-disconnect, and DM on stray polls
- AX.25 acks surface in the UI (pending TX flips on N(R) advance)
- paclen scaled by baud; YAPP DT chunks follow
- Modem state and panel layout persisted across wfweb restarts
- Shared station callsign reused across CW, FT8/FT4, FreeDV reporter,
  APRS, and the AX.25 link — set once in the gear dialog
- TX path unified with mic/FT8 (drops the 300 ms unkey guard); USB tail
  shaved by ~55 ms after a burst
- Local TX monitor so the operator hears their own outgoing audio
- Packet <-> FreeDV mutual exclusion; voice mode required when packet
  is on
- Waterfall: FT8-style palette, S0 renders as dark blue, ~60 px/s scroll
- Fix Ctrl-C shutdown: clean up dwThread and wake the AX.25 dispatcher

Documentation:
- README: new "AX.25 packet" section with capability table, RX/TX flow,
  and Direwolf attribution; comparison table and intro updated
- THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES: add Dire Wolf entry (GPL-2.0-or-later)
- resources/direwolf/README-vendoring.md: upstream commit + local patches

Testing / CI:
- New virtual rig simulator: closed-loop test bench with freq/mode-aware
  channel routing, per-link attenuation matrix, per-mode TX bandwidth
  filter, per-rig noise floor, and a web control panel on port 5900

Fixes:
- icomserver: clarify hasTxAudio setting on the config->LAN path; drop a
  noisy per-packet TX-audio debug log


v0.5.2 (2026-04-19)
--------------------

Features:
- Add LAN disconnect/reconnect UI with clean shutdown
- Add Main/Sub VFO awareness for Command29 radios (IC-7610, IC-785x,
  IC-9700, IC-905)
- Add touch and pointer event handling for spectrum and waterfall canvases
- Refactor scope drag handling for improved frequency dragging interaction

Fixes:
- Fix Power On overlay rendering during powering-on state (#33)
- Fix LAN reconnect leaving rigCaps unpopulated
- Fix VFO label/frequency desync on non-cmd29 rigs
- Fix deadlock from receiveCache routing frequency updates by VFO
- Fix UI elements not populated after LAN power-up (#19)
- Fix waterfall flash on drag release and waterfall dragging (#22)
- Fix CW decoder audio cracking on Windows browsers (#21)
- Fix Windows build: RADE Opus cmake generator and header patching

Testing / CI:
- Add integration test suite with mock Icom radio (49 tests covering USB
  and LAN paths)
- Run integration tests in all CI builds
- Per-branch dev builds with branch name in filenames and tags
- Publish dev-build pre-release on manual workflow runs

Documentation:
- Add CLAUDE.md and Claude Code commands for AI-assisted development


v0.5.1 (2026-04-11)
--------------------

Features:
- Add FreeDV Reporter integration (qso.freedv.org Socket.IO client) and
  RADE EOO callsign encoding/decoding
- Send continuous SNR updates to FreeDV Reporter while receiving
- Add monitor (MON) control via CI-V commands
- Add sidetone to DIGI TUNE and use same gain as regular TX
- Show percentages instead of raw values on gain sliders
- Accept hex CI-V addresses on --civ and drop the built-in address table

Fixes:
- Fix VFO/split commands on cmd29 rigs (IC-7610, IC-785x, IC-9700, IC-905)
- Fix RADE TX power drift caused by shared ALC-controlled gain
- Fix setCIVAddr signal/slot type mismatch
- Send freedvModes independently of rigCaps to fix LAN race
- Disable FreeDV on non-voice modes and force SSB when enabled
- Make FreeDV and FT8/DIGI modes mutually exclusive
- Reject .rig files passed to --settings with a helpful error

Documentation:
- Reorganize README with a Getting Started section
- Drop --civ from LAN examples in README and DOCKER docs


v0.5.0 (2026-04-05)
--------------------

FreeDV digital voice:
- Add FreeDV codec2 support with 700D, 700E, and 1600 modes
- Add RADE V1 neural voice codec as a FreeDV mode
- ALC control for FreeDV TX; mode cycling and TX monitor in web UI
- FreeDV button moved from FUNC menu to MODE overlay
- Hide FreeDV button when codec2 is not available

Platform support:
- FreeDV and RADE support on all platforms: Linux (Docker/native), macOS,
  and Windows
- Windows: RADE and FreeDV codec2 added to vcpkg build (build.bat)
- macOS: static-link RADE to eliminate dylib signing issues; ad-hoc
  codesign binary and dylibs; re-sign after install_name_tool patching
- Docker: RADE and FreeDV added to Docker build

Fixes:
- Fix segfault on Ctrl-C exit during FreeDV TX
- Fix FreeDV TX silence after browser restart
- Fix ALSA underruns after client disconnect during RADE/FreeDV TX
- Scale RADE TX output to match codec2 FreeDV ALC levels
- Fix RADE UI issues: stats display, logging, shutdown, and default mode
- Fix codec2 CI build: clone outside MSYS2 shell
- Fix macOS Gatekeeper block

Packaging:
- Add third-party license file (THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES) bundled in all
  packages
- Add .dockerignore to exclude host build artifacts

Documentation:
- Document macOS FreeDV and RADE build prerequisites
- Update README with FreeDV/RADE features, credits, and licenses


v0.4.2 (2026-03-29)
--------------------

Packaging:
- Add native .deb builds for Debian 12 (Bookworm) and Debian 13 (Trixie),
  fixing installation on Raspberry Pi OS Trixie (librtaudio7) (#15)
- .deb filenames now include the target distro: ubuntu2404, debian12, debian13
- Switch macOS artifact from tarball to zip

Documentation:
- Add git submodule init instructions to BUILDING.md (#15)
- Document .deb package variants and which distro each targets in README
- Add IC-7300 USB Docker quick-start example to README


v0.4.1 (2026-03-28)
--------------------

Features:
- Add memory channel browser: scan, write, recall, and clear radio memories
- MEM button in FUNC panel opens memory browser overlay
- REST API endpoint for memory recall (POST /api/v1/radio/memories/{ch}/recall)

Fixes:
- Fix filter resetting to FIL1 on every mode change from web UI
- Fix split status detection (QVariant type mismatch caused silent failures)

Notes:
- Memory recall sets VFO frequency and mode only; the radio stays in VFO mode.
  Full MEM mode is not supported because the Icom CI-V protocol has no
  read-only query for memory state, and the IC-7300 does not send unsolicited
  notifications when memory channels change from the front panel.


v0.4.0 (2026-03-26)
--------------------

Features:
- Add radio power on/off control via web UI
- Add combined P.AMP/ATT button and spectrum indicator
- Detect hardware power-off via consecutive FA errors

Fixes:
- Fix BW bar not updating when filter is changed


v0.3.6 (2026-03-24)
--------------------

Fixes:
- Fix radio menus closing by using .rig file periodic commands instead of
  hardcoded aggressive CI-V polling that saturated the bus
- Keep Power/SWR/ALC meter polling at priorityHighest for responsive meters

Enhancements:
- Shift waterfall history on frequency change to maintain signal alignment;
  band jumps clear the waterfall


v0.3.5 (2026-03-22)
--------------------

Build:
- Add macOS (Apple Silicon) build to CI and release pipeline
- Add macOS build instructions to BUILDING.md
- Enable C++17 for Eigen compatibility on macOS
- Bump GitHub Actions to Node.js 24 compatible versions

Fixes:
- Fix macOS TLS proxy truncating large responses and blocking WebSocket

Docs:
- Reorganize README: lead with screenshots and quick-start paths, highlight
  Docker for IC-7300 Mk2 Ethernet users, link to BUILDING.md for build
  instructions
- Update screenshots


v0.3.4 (2026-03-21)
--------------------

DIGI:
- Smooth ALC control: replace bang-bang controller with proportional control
  using EMA smoothing, dead zone, and asymmetric gain adjustment to eliminate
  TX power fluctuations
- Start at 25% gain instead of 100% to avoid overdriving the rig on first TX

CLI:
- Add --audio-device list option to enumerate available audio devices

Bug fixes:
- Fix auto-detection of USB Audio CODEC for rig server mode

Docs:
- Fix docs: rename wfview to wfweb in DOCKER.md, fix anchor link, add
  clearconfig flag in README


v0.3.3 (2026-03-21)
--------------------

Docker & rig server:
- Docker support: multi-arch builds, comprehensive DOCKER.md documentation
- Web and rig servers are now mutually exclusive: --no-web disables the web
  interface and enables the Icom UDP rig server for LAN clients
- Add --serial-port and --audio-system CLI flags for Docker USB access
- Add --audio-device CLI flag to override audio device selection
- Fix default audio device selection: "default" now correctly uses the
  system default device (PipeWire/PulseAudio) instead of picking an output
  monitor as input, which caused silent audio in rig server mode
- Suppress rx latency status messages from headless console output
- Upgrade Docker runtime base to Ubuntu 25.10


v0.3.2 (2026-03-20)
--------------------

LAN/UDP support:
- LAN/UDP connection support in headless mode (servermain): connect to a
  remote rig over the network without the GUI
- CLI overrides for full LAN configuration without a .ini file: --lan,
  --lan-control, --lan-serial, --lan-audio, --lan-user, --lan-pass,
  --civ, --manufacturer
- --no-server / -S flag to disable the built-in rig server when
  connecting to a remote rig that already runs one
- Audio streaming works over LAN with proper codec/sample rate config
  and 150ms latency defaults for remote buffering

CLI:
- --port / -p flag to override the web server port from the command line
- Fix --help and --version hanging (defer keyboard thread start)


v0.3.1 (2026-03-19)
--------------------

DIGI panel:
- Smooth ALC control to eliminate TX power fluctuations during FT8/FT4

Infrastructure:
- Include Windows build in release pipeline


v0.3.0 (2026-03-16)
--------------------

Windows:
- Windows build support via vcpkg (opus, portaudio, hidapi, openssl,
  eigen3, qcustomplot); build.bat script for local builds
- SSL certificate generation via OpenSSL C API on Windows (no openssl
  CLI dependency)
- USB audio capture on Windows with poll timer and COM initialization
- GitHub Actions CI: Windows build job with vcpkg caching and ZIP
  artifact upload
- BUILDING-WINDOWS.md build instructions

Fixes:
- Fix intermittent slow S-meter and delayed frequency changes: a signal
  delivery race between rigServer and servermain meant the polling setup
  block was sometimes skipped entirely on startup (no auto-information,
  no recurring polls, no queue interval recalculation); fix by setting
  rigAvailable immediately on entry to prevent the race
- Fix queue flooding from stale-cache re-requests: remove SWR
  always-re-request special case in getCache() and use addUnique()
  instead of add() to prevent duplicate immediate commands piling up


v0.2.6 (2026-03-16)
--------------------

Fixes:
- Fix slow S-meter updates in wfweb: the queue had too many meters at
  priorityHighest (5 items vs 1 in the GUI), starving S-meter polls;
  move ALC meter to priorityHigh to reduce contention


v0.2.5 (2026-03-16)
--------------------

Infrastructure:
- Rename headless binary from wfserver to wfweb; project file renamed
  from wfserver.pro to wfweb.pro
- Rename systemd/wfserver.service to systemd/wfweb.service; update
  ExecStart path and description
- Update systemd/wfweb@.service ExecStart from wfview to wfweb
- Update GitHub Actions workflow to build wfweb.pro
- Remove wfview.pro (GUI build); wfweb.pro is now the sole build target
- Update README to reflect the new binary name


v0.2.4 (2026-03-13)
--------------------

DIGI panel (FT8/FT4):
- Waterfall scroll speed reduced 4x for better readability
- Horizontal separator lines drawn at time slot boundaries
- TX/RX markers now show full signal bandwidth as semi-transparent bands
  instead of thin 3px lines; TX band turns red when armed
- Callsign labels moved to top of waterfall (below TX/RX indicators) and
  persist for 5 time slots; cleared on band change
- Fix callsign label frequency offset (~15 Hz) — labels now centered on
  the actual signal position
- ALC meter and auto-gain control for FT8/FT4 TX: gain is reduced
  automatically when ALC exceeds threshold
- Local TX monitor volume reduced to avoid clipping
- DIGI panel stays open during rig-initiated mode changes
- Removed separate DIGI Log button (use shared QSO Log instead)

Web UI:
- Shared QSO log panel for CW, SSB, and FT8/FT4 with editable fields
- Filter settings panel with bandwidth, PBT, and filter shape controls
- MIC GAIN slider added to the GAIN panel
- Fix duplicate CW progress bar when re-clicking a memory button
- Fix DIGI panel visibility on mode change and panel restore
- Fix blank entry appearing on QSO log edit


v0.2.3 (2026-03-08)
--------------------

REST API:
- New plain-HTTP REST API at /api/v1/radio/* for scripting, automation, and
  microcontroller integration (ESP32, Pico W, Arduino — no TLS required)
- In SSL mode a second HTTP listener binds the WebSocket port so curl/scripts
  can reach the API without a TLS stack
- Endpoints: frequency, mode, VFO (select/swap/equalize), PTT, meters (S/SWR/power),
  gains (AF/RF/power/squelch), RX DSP (preamp, NB, NR, AGC, auto-notch, filter
  width), TX settings (split, tuner, compressor, monitor), CW send/stop
- Full combined status via GET /api/v1/radio; CORS headers on all responses
- Fix: buffer incoming data per-socket so requests fragmented across TCP
  segments are fully reassembled before parsing

DIGI panel (FT8/FT4):
- Auto-tune to standard FT8/FT4 calling frequency when the DIGI panel is
  opened, matched by nearest VFO within 500 kHz
- Block self-QSO clicks: clicking a decode row transmitted by MY CALL is
  now a no-op

Audio:
- Fix mic audio loss after FT8 TX: FT8 completion no longer tears down the
  USB audio path when the user mic is active; mic frames are suppressed
  during TX without closing the AudioWorklet session
- Remove over-aggressive ALSA IdleState watchdog that dropped mic frames
  after any buffer underrun; ALSA's own snd_pcm_recover handles transients
- MIC OFF overlay is now a persistent MIC ON/OFF toggle button

Documentation:
- REST_API.md: full endpoint reference with curl examples, response schemas,
  port table, and shell scripting recipes


v0.2.2 (2026-03-03)
--------------------

DIGI panel (FT8/FT4):
- Fix TX double-fire regression: user-initiated TX uses a 13 s slot window
  while auto re-arm reverts to 4.5 s, preventing the same slot firing twice
- Fix TX waterfall splatter and add local TX audio monitor
- Fix auto-QSO cycle, TX slot-window logic, and QSO logging state machine

Audio:
- Fix ALSA underruns during FT8 TX (USB audio path): server-side pre-buffer
  accumulates PCM chunks until the ALSA buffer is full before starting
  playback; IdleState watchdog stops the device cleanly when the buffer
  drains at end of TX, eliminating snd_pcm_recover underruns

Infrastructure:
- ft8ts submodule updated to v0.0.12; upstream ships the pack28 fix
  (short callsigns like K1FM no longer corrupted); local vendored patch removed
- CI: overwrite release assets on re-tag


v0.2.1 (2026-03-02)
--------------------

Infrastructure:
- ft8ts: vendor patched dist locally pending upstream fix for issue #1
  (pack28 bug corrupting 4-character callsigns like K1FM)
- README: FT8 screenshot, vertical mobile screenshots, CW/FT8 feature rows


v0.2.0 (2026-03-01)
--------------------

DIGI panel (FT8/FT4):
- Fix marker/signal alignment: markers now point to the visual centre of the
  tone span rather than tone 0, correcting a ~12 Hz low bias
- TX waterfall loopback: the transmitted signal is now visible in the DIGI
  waterfall during TX (locally generated samples fed into the FFT pipeline)
- QSO logged indicator: a green confirmation row is appended to the Directed
  panel whenever a QSO is logged (manually or automatically)
- Version string: console log now shows "WFWEB" with the server version
  received at connect time; hardcoded date/version string removed
- Waterfall frequency range: display now spans 300-2800 Hz (was 0-3000 Hz),
  with matching scale labels, input bounds, FFT bin mapping, and click handler
- Layout: Directed and QSO Messages columns merged into a single right column
- Mobile: long-press (500 ms) on a decode row triggers the same action as
  double-click on desktop; haptic feedback via navigator.vibrate(40)
- CQ calling controls added; double-click arm supported in QSO Messages panel
- Decoded frames sorted by decreasing SNR within each slot
- Web Worker used for FT8/FT4 decode to keep the UI thread responsive
- Waterfall frequency labels; TX/RX UX and QSO state machine fixes
- RX frequency control; smarter row-click handling; auto-desist on busy DX
- Panel rationalization; FT8/USB-only enforcement; deferred TX re-arm fix
- Mobile UI tweaks: no waterfall callsigns on small screens, stacked CQ
  buttons, message-only decode rows

Web UI:
- Panel rationalization and layout cleanup


